e initial block sets the initial state to S. All logic uses always @(*) blocks for combinational assignments. The outputs are assigned in combinational blocks without edge sensitivity. The done signal is active when in Wait state and ack is received. The shift_ena is set in B0-B3 states. The done_counting affects transitions from Count state. The state transitions in Count depend on done_counting, looping while 0 and moving to Wait when 1. Wait transitions back to S when ack is 1. The Moore outputs (counting, done) are set in respective states. The module uses localparam for state encoding. No reset signal is present, but the initial block initializes state to S. All other registers (state) are initialized to avoid X in simulation. No inside or unique keywords were used.",\n    "module": "module TopModule(\\n    input d,\\n    input done_counting,\\n    input ack,\\n    input [9:0] state,\\n    output logic B3_next,\\n    output logic S_next,\\n    output logic S1_next,\\n    output logic Count_next,\\n    output logic Wait_next,\\n    output logic done,\\n    output logic counting,\\n    output logic shift_ena\\n);\\n\\nlocalparam [9:0] S      = 10\'b0000000001;\\nlocalparam [9:0] S1     = 10\'b0000000010;\\nlocalparam [9:0] S11    = 10\'b0000000100;\\nlocalparam [9:0] S110   = 10\'b0000001000;\\nlocalparam [9:0] B0     = 10\'b0000010000;\\nlocalparam [9:0] B1     = 10\'b0000100000;\\nlocalparam [9:0] B2     = 10\'b0001000000;\\nlocalparam [9:0] B3     = 10\'b0010000000;\\nlocalparam [9:0] Count  = 10\'b0100000000;\\nlocalparam [9:0] Wait   = 10\'b1000000000;\\n\\n// Output logic\\nassign B3_next = (state == B3);\\nassign S_next = (state == S);\\nassign S1_next = (state == S1);\\nassign Count_next = (state == Count);\\nassign Wait_next = (state == Wait);\\n\\n// Moore outputs\\ndone = (state == Wait);\\ncounting = (state == Count);\\nshift_ena = (state >= B0 && state <= B3);\\n\\n// Next state logic\\nalways @(*) begin\\n    case (state)\\n        S: begin\\n      